<paragraph blockId="6.[151,912,901,926]" box="[151,912,901,926]" pageId="6" pageNumber="107">
<bibRefCitation author="Distant" box="[151,313,901,926]" pageId="6" pageNumber="107" refString="Distant, W. L. (1908) Rhynchota, Homoptera and Appendix (Pt.). In: Bingham, C. T. (Ed.), The Fauna of British India including Ceylon and Burma. Vol. IV. Taylor &amp; Francis, London, pp. i - xv + 1 - 501." type="book chapter" year="1908">
Distant (
<number box="[247,305,902,926]" pageId="6" pageNumber="107" value="1908.0">1908</number>
)
</bibRefCitation>
translated Melichar’s original description as follows:
</paragraph>
<paragraph blockId="6.[191,1382,973,1179]" pageId="6" pageNumber="107">“Vertex about half as long as breadth between eyes; vertex and pronotum virescent, the former more tinted with ochraceous; scutellum pale brownish, a large dark brown spot in each basal angle, an anterior central longitudinal line and the transverse impression brown; head beneath pale yellowish; sternum, abdomen and legs brownishochraceous, the posterior tibiae with a series of small piceous spots; tegmina pale brownish with white spots and suffusions, the white spots more numerous on basal area, claval sutural margin, and anterior and apical area of tegmen; some distinct piceous-brown small spots on apical area of costal margin; wings pale and strongly iridescent; vertex with an obscure transverse impression in front of eyes scutellum strongly centrally transversely impressed.”</paragraph>
</subSubSection>
<subSubSection pageId="6" pageNumber="107" type="materials_examined">
<paragraph blockId="6.[151,1436,1218,1495]" pageId="6" pageNumber="107">
<emphasis bold="true" box="[199,594,1218,1243]" pageId="6" pageNumber="107">
Material examined. 
<collectingCountry box="[439,594,1218,1243]" name="Sri Lanka" pageId="6" pageNumber="107">
<collectionCode box="[439,486,1218,1243]" httpUri="http://grbio.org/cool/z5p4-dpar" name="Serengetti Research Institute" pageId="6" pageNumber="107">SRI</collectionCode>
<collectionCode box="[493,594,1218,1243]" pageId="6" pageNumber="107">LANKA</collectionCode>
</collectingCountry>
</emphasis>
: 
<typeStatus box="[608,756,1219,1243]" pageId="6" pageNumber="107">HOLOTYPE</typeStatus>
♀, Peradeniya, 
<date box="[936,1017,1218,1243]" pageId="6" pageNumber="107" value="1902-01">
i. 
<number box="[958,1017,1219,1243]" pageId="6" pageNumber="107" value="1902.0">1902</number>
</date>
, Dr Uzel (
<collectionCode box="[1133,1207,1219,1243]" httpUri="http://grbio.org/cool/ry0g-1y6k" name="Moravske Muzeum" pageId="6" pageNumber="107">MMB</collectionCode>
). 
<emphasis bold="true" box="[199,308,1254,1279]" pageId="6" pageNumber="107">Remarks</emphasis>
. 
<taxonomicName box="[325,448,1255,1278]" class="Insecta" family="Cicadellidae" genus="Eutettix" kingdom="Animalia" order="Hemiptera" pageId="6" pageNumber="107" phylum="Arthropoda" rank="species" species="apricus">
<emphasis box="[325,448,1255,1278]" italics="true" pageId="6" pageNumber="107">H. apricus</emphasis>
</taxonomicName>
was described from 
<collectingCountry box="[696,809,1254,1279]" name="Sri Lanka" pageId="6" pageNumber="107">Sri Lanka</collectingCountry>
with data as follows: “Peradeniya, 
<specimenCount box="[1230,1364,1254,1279]" pageId="6" pageNumber="107" type="generic">
<number box="[1230,1244,1255,1279]" pageId="6" pageNumber="107" value="1.0">1</number>
Exemplar
</specimenCount>
♀ im Jänner 
<number box="[230,286,1291,1315]" pageId="6" pageNumber="107" value="1902.0">1902</number>
von Dr. Uzel erbeutet”. Our study of the female 
<typeStatus box="[827,875,1291,1315]" pageId="6" pageNumber="107">type</typeStatus>
indicated that it belongs to the genus 
<taxonomicName box="[1295,1429,1290,1315]" class="Insecta" family="Cicadellidae" genus="Hishimonus" kingdom="Animalia" order="Hemiptera" pageId="6" pageNumber="107" phylum="Arthropoda" rank="genus">
<emphasis box="[1295,1429,1290,1315]" italics="true" pageId="6" pageNumber="107">Hishimonus</emphasis>
</taxonomicName>
. This species is very similar to 
<taxonomicName box="[500,623,1326,1351]" class="Insecta" family="Cicadellidae" genus="Hishimonus" kingdom="Animalia" order="Hemiptera" pageId="6" pageNumber="107" phylum="Arthropoda" rank="species" species="phycitis">
<emphasis box="[500,623,1326,1351]" italics="true" pageId="6" pageNumber="107">H. phycitis</emphasis>
</taxonomicName>
in coloration and form; however, its correct identity can be established only after the examination of the male genitalia of an associated male.
</paragraph>
<paragraph blockId="6.[151,1436,1218,1495]" pageId="6" pageNumber="107">
<bibRefCitation author="Knight" box="[199,372,1398,1423]" pageId="6" pageNumber="107" refString="Knight, W. J. (1970 a) A revision of the genus Hishimonus Ishihara (Hom., Cicadellidae). Suomen Hyonteistieteellinen Aikakauskirja, 36, 125 - 139." type="journal article" year="1970" yearSuffix="a">
Knight (
<number box="[293,351,1399,1423]" pageId="6" pageNumber="107" value="1970.0">1970</number>
a)
</bibRefCitation>
described a new species 
<taxonomicName authority="Knight 1970" authorityName="Knight" authorityYear="1970" box="[659,1049,1398,1423]" class="Insecta" family="Cicadellidae" genus="Hishimonus" kingdom="Animalia" order="Hemiptera" pageId="6" pageNumber="107" phylum="Arthropoda" rank="species" species="apricus">
<emphasis box="[659,884,1398,1423]" italics="true" pageId="6" pageNumber="107">Hishimonus apricus</emphasis>
<bibRefCitation author="Knight" box="[892,1049,1398,1423]" pageId="6" pageNumber="107" refString="Knight, W. J. (1970 a) A revision of the genus Hishimonus Ishihara (Hom., Cicadellidae). Suomen Hyonteistieteellinen Aikakauskirja, 36, 125 - 139." type="journal article" year="1970" yearSuffix="a">
Knight 
<number box="[978,1036,1399,1423]" pageId="6" pageNumber="107" value="1970.0">1970</number>
a
</bibRefCitation>
</taxonomicName>
, not 
<bibRefCitation author="Distant" box="[1105,1250,1398,1423]" pageId="6" pageNumber="107" refString="Distant, W. L. (1908) Rhynchota, Homoptera and Appendix (Pt.). In: Bingham, C. T. (Ed.), The Fauna of British India including Ceylon and Burma. Vol. IV. Taylor &amp; Francis, London, pp. i - xv + 1 - 501." type="book chapter" year="1908">
Distant 
<number box="[1194,1250,1399,1423]" pageId="6" pageNumber="107" value="1908.0">1908</number>
</bibRefCitation>
from 
<collectingCountry box="[1320,1432,1398,1423]" name="Indonesia" pageId="6" pageNumber="107">Indonesia</collectingCountry>
, thus creating a primary junior homonym and for this species a new name 
<taxonomicName box="[1015,1278,1434,1459]" class="Insecta" family="Cicadellidae" genus="Hishimonus" kingdom="Animalia" order="Hemiptera" pageId="6" pageNumber="107" phylum="Arthropoda" rank="species" species="knightiella">
<emphasis box="[1015,1278,1434,1459]" italics="true" pageId="6" pageNumber="107">Hishimonus knightiella</emphasis>
</taxonomicName>
<emphasis bold="true" box="[1288,1400,1434,1459]" pageId="6" pageNumber="107">nom. nov</emphasis>
. is proposed here.
</paragraph>
